<def f='qtbase-6.5.0/src/widgets/kernel/qsizepolicy.h' l='82' type='void QSizePolicy::setWidthForHeight(bool b)'/>
<doc f='qtbase-6.5.0/src/widgets/kernel/qsizepolicy.cpp' l='243'>/*!
    \fn void QSizePolicy::setWidthForHeight(bool dependent)

    Sets the flag determining whether the widget&apos;s width
    depends on its height, to \a dependent.

    This is only supported for QGraphicsLayout&apos;s subclasses.
    It is not possible to have a layout with both height-for-width
    and width-for-height constraints at the same time.

    \sa hasWidthForHeight(), setHeightForWidth()
*/</doc>
